---
title: Vegan Harissa Apricot–Glazed Tofu with Green Beans, Lemon Cilantro Couscous & Pistachios
description: Savory tofu is the star of this flavor-packed meal. Season, coat, and pan-fry it into crisp, golden nuggets with pillowy-soft interiors, then drape in a tangy-spicy-sweet apricot-harissa glaze. Fragrant cilantro lemon couscous provides a tasty bed to nestle the glazed tofu alongside tender oven-roasted green beans. Finish with a shower of crunchy pistachios and a bright squeeze of lemon for the ultimate vegan dinner idea.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/vegan-harissa-apricotglazed-tofu-eb3a562f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/vegan-harissa-apricotglazed-tofu-63c6ca9f1767dbf3590fb50a-bd706d4b.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-harissa-apricotglazed-tofu-63c6ca9f1767dbf3590fb50a
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 380 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

In a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings), combine @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, half the @veggie stock concentrate{2}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low; cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, pat @tofu{1} dry with #paper towels{}; dice into 1/2-inch cubes.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss tofu with @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}; season generously with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add tofu and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and crispy, ~{3-4%minutes}. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches.)

Reduce heat to low; stir in @apricot jam{1}, remaining stock concentrates, 1/3 cup water, @harissa powder{1/4%tsp}, and a squeeze of lemon juice. (For 4 servings, use 2/3 cup water, ½ tsp harissa powder, and juice from half a lemon.) Simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Remove from heat; season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in cilantro, lemon zest, juice from half a lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), @olive oil{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of salt.

Divide couscous, tofu, and green beans between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with pistachios and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.